snippet.title: AQUAMAN - Final Trailer - Now Playing In Theaters
snippet.description:
www.Facebook.com/AquamanMovie
www.Twitter.com/AquamanMovie
www.Instagram.com/AquamanMovie
www.AquamanMovie.com

From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger.  The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Wan Film, ‚ÄúAquaman.‚Äù  The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018, in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Reacts To Losing in Court Against Johnny Depp | Amber Heard Reaction On Losing Her Case
snippet.description:
Months after losing a libel case against British newspaper Johnny Depp has won a legal battle against Amber Heard, his former wife.

Johnny Depp or Amber Heard have not reacted to the ruling on their social media accounts.

The actor has been granted a motion to establish whether or not the "Aquaman" actress donated her $7 million divorce settlement to a charity.

The ruling,given by a judge in New York, said American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) must provide documentation that confirms whether Amber Heard gave the non-profit organisation a donation from the $7 million she received in her divorce settlement from Depp as well as the Children's Hospital Los Angeles.

‚ÄúMr. Depp is most gratified by the Court‚Äôs decision," Depp's attorney told USA TODAY.

snippet.localized.description:
Months after losing a libel case against British newspaper Johnny Depp has won a legal battle against Amber Heard, his former wife.

Johnny Depp or Amber Heard have not reacted to the ruling on their social media accounts.

The actor has been granted a motion to establish whether or not the "Aquaman" actress donated her $7 million divorce settlement to a charity.

The ruling,given by a judge in New York, said American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) must provide documentation that confirms whether Amber Heard gave the non-profit organisation a donation from the $7 million she received in her divorce settlement from Depp as well as the Children's Hospital Los Angeles.

‚ÄúMr. Depp is most gratified by the Court‚Äôs decision," Depp's attorney told USA TODAY.

Amber Heard had given evidence against Depp in  the actor's case against the British newspaper which the Hollywood star was suing for calling him wife beater.

snippet.title: Aquaman (2018) | Movie Trailer 1 | Warner Bros. Pictures | Jason Momoa, Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe
snippet.description:
Born upon the shores of the surface world, Arthur Curry (Jason Momoa) discovers that he is only half human, with the other half of his blood being of Atlanteean descent, thus making him the rightful heir to the throne of the undersea kingdom of Atlantis. However, Arthur learns that Atlantis is being ruled by his malicious half-brother Orm (Patrick Wilson), who seeks to unite the seven underwater kingdoms and wage war upon the surface. With aid from Nuidis Vulko (Willem Dafoe) and the gorgeous Mera (Amber Heard), Arthur must discover the full potential of his true destiny and become Aquaman in order to save Atlantis and the surface from Orm's evil plot.

snippet.title: AQUAMAN ‚Äì Final Trailer ‚Äì Warner Bros  UK
snippet.description:
#aquaman #superficialcollection
Http://www.Facebook.com/AquamanMovie
Http:// www.Twitter.com/AquamanMovie 
Http:// www.Instagram.com/AquamanMovie
Http://www.AquamanMovie.com

From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role. The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger. The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù). They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).

snippet.title: AQUAMAN - Extended Video
snippet.description:
Guarda il nuovo extended video di Aquaman.
Al cinema dal 1 gennaio.

Da Warner Bros. Pictures e il regista James Wan arriva un‚Äôavventura visivamente mozzafiato nel mondo sottomarino dei sette mari, AQUAMAN, interpretato da Jason Momoa nel ruolo del protagonista. Il film rivela la storia delle origini del mezzo ‚Äì umano, mezzo atlantideo Arthur Curry e lo accompagna nel viaggio della sua vita, che non solo lo costringer√† ad affrontare chi √® veramente, ma anche a scoprire se √® degno di essere ci√≤ per cui √® nato‚Ä¶ un re.

Il film vede la partecipazione di Amber Heard (Justice League, Magic Mike XXL) nei panni di Mera, una guerriera del fuoco e alleata di AQUAMAN per tutto il suo viaggio; Willem Dafoe (Plotone, Spider-Man 2) √® Vulko, consigliere al trono di Atlantide; Patrick Wilson (The Conjuring, Watchmen) √® Orm/Ocean Master, l‚Äôattuale Re di Atlantide; Dolph Lundgren (I Mercenari) come Nereus, re della trib√π di Atlantide Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (The Get Down su Netflix) nei panni del vendicativo Black Manta; e la vincitrice dell‚ÄôOscar Nicole Kidman (The Hours, Lion) come la mamma di Arthrur, Atlanna; cos√¨ come Ludi Lin (Power Rangers) come Captain Murk, comandante di Atlantide; e Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episodio II ‚Äì L‚ÄôAttacco Dei Cloni‚Äù ‚ÄúLanterna Verde‚Äù) sar√† il padre di Arthur, Tom Curry.

James Wan dirige da una sceneggiatura di David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (The Conjuring 2) e Will Beall (Gangstar Squad, serie tv Training Day), da una storia di Geoff Johns, James Wan e Will Beal, basata sul personaggio DC Aquaman, creato da Paul Norris e Mort Weisnger.
Il film √® prodotto da Peter Safran e Rob Cowan, con Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns e Walter Hamada come produttori esecutivi.

Il team di Wan include il direttore della fotografia candidato all‚ÄôOscar Don Burgess (The Conjuring 2, Forrest Gump), lo scenografo Bill Brzeski (Furious 7), la costumista Kym Barrett (trilogia di Matrix, The Amazing Spider-Man) e il compositore Rupert Gregson-Williams (Wonder Woman).

Il film uscir√† nelle sale il 1¬∞ gennaio 2019, in 3D, 2D e IMAX, e sar√† distribuito in tutto il mondo dalla Warner Bros. Pictures.

snippet.title: Celebrities EXPOSE Amber Heard and Side With Johnny Depp!
snippet.description:
It cannot be denied that Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs failed marriage tops a long list of the worst divorces in the history of Hollywood today.  And in Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs case, the consequences of their tumultuous marriage still feels its blown up to this day, after it started in 2016. That‚Äôs a pretty long time. Yes, after almost five years of going back and forth in court, they are still in it. And during these five long years, the two have been supported by their own fans, friends, co-workers, and families. However, in terms of supporters, it is pretty obvious that Johnny Depp has a lot more advantages than his former wife. And in terms of celebrities with huge names in the industry, Johnny Depp seems to be also winning their hearts. Due to these ongoing court rulings and scandals involving these big names in the industry, the case is greatly affecting Johnny‚Äôs career, and one example was when he was asked to resign from his role as Grindelwald in the third installment of J.K Rowling‚Äôs Fantastic Beasts film trilogy that was supposed to be released in 2022.  Due to this, many other actors perceived this as ‚Äúunfair‚Äù treatment of Depp, many stars stepped out to defend him. Many fans, friends, and co-stars defended him and what was shocking was even his previous lovers and wives stepped up to speak for him, even two of his former flames Vanessa Paradis whom he had two children with, and Winona Ryder, his love team and long time girlfriend in the 90s. Yet, as the issue continues to grow bigger and bigger, it involves more and more people as well, and more and more celebrities continue to arise and speak out on social media about the issue. So who are these brave celebs who are not buying Amber‚Äôs lies? Watch this video to find out. But before anything else, please make sure to hit that subscribe button first and ring that notification bell for more updates on the infamous Johnny Depp and Amber Heard upcoming trial. Now, let‚Äôs dig in!

As the trial is coming near, the issue that has somehow been buried deep in the internet has recently surfaced once again, and guess who‚Äôs been the subject of ridicule these past few weeks, or months, rather? You guessed that right, Amber Heard. Amber seemed to have been losing more and more of her supporters. Then there was evidence of her having affairs with an actor and a multi-billionaire, James Franco and Elon Musk. But what upset most people was the fact that Johnny Depp was forced to step down from his role as Grindelwald in the upcoming third franchise of the film trilogy ‚ÄúFantastic Beasts‚Äù. But now that Johnny has been removed from his role, people‚Äôs fury shot directly at Amber Heard, as she was going back to reprise her role in the second franchise of the DC Extended Universe film Aquaman, despite the lawsuits she is currently facing. Some even started a petition to request Warner Bros. to fire Amber Heard, the same way they did to Johnny. 

1. Penelope Cruz
Penelope is a Spanish actress known for her beauty and her portrayal of sultry characters. She achieved early success in Spanish cinema and quickly established herself as an international star, co-starring with Johnny Depp in Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides and Blow. As his co-actor, Penelope supports Depp from the start.

2. Sia
Singer and songwriter Sia has also voiced her ‚Äúpublic support‚Äù for Johnny Depp as the actor prepares for his defamation trial against ex-wife Amber Heard. The singer, unprompted, shared her support for Depp in a Twitter post which read: ‚ÄúJust showing my public support for Johnny Depp.‚Äù

3. Kevin McNally
Kevin Robert McNally is an English actor, who has worked in theatre and radio extensively, as well as in film and television. For Disney, he plays Joshamee Gibbs in the Pirates of the Caribbean franchise, being one of the three actors to appear in all five films.

4. Sharon Osborne
Sharon Osborne was one of Johnny‚Äôs first supporters even from the start of the Johnny and Amber Heard issue. She was also one of the many celebrities who stood up against British news publisher.

5. Paul Bettany
Let's move on to Jonny's co-star from the 2010 movie The Tourist, Paul Bettany.

Johnny continues to earn more and more supporters. Apart from this, fans and other celebs who support the actor also continue to add up in number, especially as the release of Aquaman 2 draws near, bearing the face of Amber Heard in a lead role as Queen Mera, alongside famous faces like Jason Momoa and Nicole Kidman. 

That‚Äôs all for today, and if you enjoyed that video, and smash that subscribe button and notification bell for more videos like this.

snippet.title: Aquaman Mother Fight Scene In Hindi ||Aquaman Full Movie Fight Scene In Hindi
snippet.description:
Aquaman Mother Fight Scene In Hindi ||Aquaman Full Movie Fight Scene In Hindi

Aquaman is a 2018 American superhero film based on the DC Comics character of the same name. Distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures, it is the sixth film in the DC Extended Universe (DCEU). The film was directed by James Wan, from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick and Will Beall. It stars Jason Momoa as Arthur Curry / Aquaman, who sets out to lead the underwater kingdom of Atlantis and stop his half-brother, King Orm, from uniting the seven underwater kingdoms to destroy the surface world. Amber Heard, Willem Dafoe, Patrick Wilson, Dolph Lundgren, Ludi Lin, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II, Temuera Morrison and Nicole Kidman appear in supporting roles.
Development began in 2004 but did not gain traction until Man of Steel was released in 2013. In August 2014, Beall and Kurt Johnstad were hired to write competing scripts. Wan signed on as director in April 2015, and in July 2016, the film moved forward with Beall's screenplay. The main cast was confirmed through 2016 and early 2017. Principal photography began in Australia in May 2017, taking place at Village Roadshow Studios on the Gold Coast, Queensland, Australia, with additional production teams in Canada, Italy and Morocco. Filming concluded the following October. Several vendors provided visual effects, ranging from high-detail hair simulations to the creation of CGI animals and locations.

snippet.title: Amber Heard 2021 New
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Fired From Jason Momoa‚Äôs Blockbuster Franchise Following the Johnny Depp Row

Amber Heard and Johnny Depp's divorce was major news a few months back. Following the lawsuit, Johnny Depp had to face a lot of trouble on the professional front and his fans were not at all happy about it. Depp had lost a libel case against The Sun over a headline that ascribed him as a "wife-beater." which further resulted in Warner Bros. asking him to resign from Fantastic Beasts 3. This was not taken well by his fans who then started a petition calling for the removal of Amber Heard from Warner Bros' Aquaman 2. Now, rumour has it that this might become true. Following the Johnny Depp Row, Petition to Remove Amber Heard From Aquaman 2 Crosses 1 Million Signatures!

Also Read | Zack Snyder‚Äôs Justice League Trailer: Batman, Superman, Wonder Woman and Other DC Superheroes Team Up for Some Action, Joker Adds Hint of Evil (Watch Video)

While the petition or the libel might not be the reason for Amber's exit from the film, it has been learned that she indeed has been fired from the film. Reports suggest that Amber gained a little weight before the commencement of the shoot and the makers are not keen on continuing to work with her. Not just that, it is being said that Emilia Clarke who I known popularly for her role as Daenerys Targaryen from Game Of Thrones is all set to replace her. Amber essayed the character of Mera in the Jason Mamoa starrer.

A source told Australian site Sausage Roll, "Amber Heard did not pass her physical examination. She‚Äôs put on some pounds and is in terrible shape. There is a clause in her contract which says she is required to be in good form ahead of shooting and she violated that." It was also revealed that Amber's role was a very demanding one in terms of action and stunts and the production house terminated the contract after seeing how the actress was not in shape to take up the role. Popcorned Planet confirmed the same but no clarity on Emilia Clarke being a replacement for the actress has been given yet. Fans Trend 'Justice For Johny Depp' After Audio Clip Of Amber Heard Admitting She Hit Him Surfaces.

Also Read | Zack Snyder's Justice League: Director Confirms Streaming Date of 'Snyder Cut' on HBO Max Through Intriguing Posters!

Talking about the petition, addressed to Courtney Simmons, SVP of Publicity & Communications for DC Warner Bros. and Paul McGuire, Corporate Communications of DC Entertainment - discusses how Amber is a domestic abuser and Warner Brothers should not glamorize her anymore. The petition has already crossed the 1 million signatures mark!

Earlier in 2019, it was reported that Depp had called on Warner Bros. to remove Amber from Aquaman. But this plea did not work in his favour and Amber went on to co-star in the billion-dollar superhero blockbuster film as Mera. Aquaman 2 arrives in theatres on December 16, 2022.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Reportedly Fired From ‚ÄòAquaman‚Äô For Reasons Unrelated to Depp
snippet.description:
For the past year or so,¬†Pirates of the Caribbean¬†Captain Jack Sparrow actor, Johnny Depp, and his ex-wife, Amber Heard, have gotten more than their fair share of negative press.
Following a report that he had allegedly abused Heard on multiple occasions, Depp filed a lawsuit against U.K. News Group Newspaper publication,¬†The Sun,¬†purporting that he was never the instigator of any domestic violence.¬†He lost the lawsuit in November 2020, but an appeal is expected.
It is worth noting that two of Depp‚Äôs former parters, Winona Ryder and Vanessa Paradis,¬†both supported the actor¬†throughout the libel case.

Depp‚Äôs lawyer and the actor himself continue to claim there was never any spousal abuse, while Heard and her camp¬†allege that she was held ‚Äúhostage‚Äù in Australia¬†during the filming of a¬†Pirates of the Caribbean¬†movie, among other things.

Depp ‚Äî¬†whose finger was cut off during an argument at one point¬†in the tumultuous relationship ‚Äî¬†has been blacklisted by many of the movie studios who previously worked with him.

Walt Disney Studios has¬†reportedly replaced him with Margot Robbie¬†in the upcoming¬†Pirates of the Caribbean 6¬†project. Meanwhile, Warner Bros.‚Äô¬†Harry Potter Fantastic¬†Beasts franchise recast Gellert Grindelwald¬†with Mads Mikkelsen (Rogue One: A Star Wars Story) after the libel trial ended.

Many of Johnny Depp‚Äôs fans believe that Heard should face the same industry backlash. A petition for her to be fired from Warner Bros.‚Äô film adaptations of DC Comics‚Äô¬†Aquaman¬†franchise¬†has garnered wide support, with nearly two million signatures.

Now, as¬†Yahoo! News¬†shared, Heard has reportedly been let go from her role as Mera ‚Äî but not for the reasons you probably think:
At this time, Warner Bros. has not confirmed Heard‚Äôs exit from the¬†Aquaman 2¬†movie. Per¬†IMDb, Heard also played Mera in Zack Snyder‚Äôs¬†Justice League, which recently finished filming.

For Depp‚Äôs part, the actor‚Äôs best hope for a career revival is likely to be¬†longtime friend and professional partner, Tim Burton. The director has cast Depp in numerous projects over the years. Burton is currently working on¬†Beetlejuice 2¬†and an¬†Addams Family¬†TV adaptation¬†‚Äî Depp‚Äôs name has been connected to both projects.

There is a beautiful colourful world around us and it will be good, I think, for you to learn some English words and phrases to be able to talk about it.

In this English lesson you'll words and phrases like paint, a fresh coat of paint, palette, visible spectrum, swatch, infrared, and more!

I hope you enjoy this English lesson about colour!

snippet.title: Amber Heard Confirms Involvement in Aquaman 2 [Explain in Hindi ]
snippet.description:
Amber Heard From Aquaman 2 [Explain in Hindi ]
Petition to Remove Amber Heard From Aquaman 2 Crosses Million-Signature Mark
A petition calling on Warner Bros. to remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2 as a result of her issues with Johnny Depp has crossed 1 million signatures.Amber Heard says she's all in to reprise her role as Mera in Aquaman 2, even as rumors of her firing circulate online and an old Change.org petition calling for such a move on Warner Bros.' part tops 1 million signatures.Heard said the sequel to the 2018 DC Extended Universe film may start production in 2021. A production start date is not conformed, as studio approval for Aquaman 2 and its cast are still pending at Warner Bros.

Speculation over Heard's involvement in Aquaman 2 heated up as her contentious relationship with ex-husband Johnny Depp continued to generate headlines since their 2017 divorce. Each has accused the other of physical abuse. Depp was recently asked to resign from Warner Bros.' Fantastic Beasts franchise of Harry Potter spinoff films after losing a libel lawsuit against British tabloid The Sun, which wrote about alleged incidents during his two-year marriage to Heard. Depp plans to appeal the libel case, and reportedly will collect his full salary for Fantastic Beasts 3, as he filmed one scene before his departure. Additionally, Depp filed a similar defamation suit against Heard in the U.S. state of Virginia, which is expected to go to trial next year.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Pissed Johnny Depp Was Kept In ‚ÄòFantastic Beasts‚Äô After Alleged Domestic Abuse?
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Pissed Johnny Depp Was Kept In ‚ÄòFantastic Beasts‚Äô After Alleged Domestic Abuse?
Right now is an incredibly validating time for victims of abuse. From TIME‚Äôs Person of The Year being the ‚ÄúSilence Breakers‚Äù to men like Matt Lauer, Charlie Rose, and Harvey Weinstein losing their jobs over sexual assault allegations, victims‚Äô stories are finally being taken as seriously as they should be. That is, if the stories came out after this movement began. Amber Heard, 31, is still waiting to have her accusations against Johnny Depp, 54, be acknowledged by the film industry, and she just spoke out about how she feels that her alleged abuser currently has a major role in the works.

Johnny is set to play the title character in Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes Of Grindelwald, and J.K. Rowling, Warner Bros., and director David Yates defended their choice not to recast him in light of Amber‚Äôs accusations of emotional and physical abuse from 2016. After Warner Bros. went on record defending their choice, Amber posted her own reaction on Twitter. ‚ÄúFor the record, this was our FULL joint statement.To pick&choose certain lines & quote them out of context, is not right.Women, stay strong,‚Äù the actress captioned an image of her and Johnny‚Äôs divorce statement. See her tweet below.

The response was a clear dig at Warner Bros. for using a part of her statement as a defense for continuing to work with a man who‚Äôs been accused of abuse. By saying ‚ÄúWomen, stay strong,‚Äù Amber sent a powerful message about how even though victims‚Äô stories are finally being heard, there are still plenty that aren‚Äôt.

The Warner Bros.‚Äô statement that Amber responded to said that they were ‚Äúaware of reports that surfaced‚Äù and ‚Äútake seriously the complexity of the issues involved‚Äù before bringing up Johnny and Amber‚Äôs joint statement about the dissolution of their marriage. ‚ÄúThis matter has been jointly addressed by both parties, in a statement in which they said ‚ÄòThere was never any intent of physical or emotional harm.‚Äô Based on the circumstances and the information available to us, we, along with the filmmakers, continue to support the decision to proceed with Johnny Depp in the role of Grindelwald in this and future films,‚Äù the statement said. While women‚Äôs stories of abuse are finally being heard, the decision to keep Johnny in the Fantastic Beasts sequel proves we still have a long way to go.

snippet.title: Petition to Remove Amber Heard From Aquaman 2 Surpasses 1.5 Million Signatures
snippet.description:
Subscribe I n  News English YouTube Channel To All The Big News Of The World.

A petition seeking to have Amber Heard removed from Warner Bros.' Aquaman 2 recently surpassed 1.5 million signatures.

The Change.org petition was created several years ago, in the wake of Heard's messy divorce from Johnny Depp and reports that both actors were physically violent during their tumultuous relationship. The petition is addressed to Courtney Simmons, SVP of Publicity & Communications for DC Warner Bros. and Paul McGuire, Corporate Communications of DC Entertainment.

It read in part, "In his $50 million lawsuit, Johnny Depp describes many incidents of domestic abuse that he suffered at the hands of his (then) wife Amber Heard, including one incident where she punched him twice in the face and another where she shattered his finger with a vodka bottle, and his finger had to be surgically reattached. He will bear the scar from that for the rest of his life."

The author of the petition further explained that Heard "was arrested in 2009 for abusing a former domestic partner, Tasya Van Ree" and alleged that the actor has "systematically crusaded to ruin Depp in Hollywood, repeating multiple accounts of fake incidents in which she had actually abused Johnny Depp, but lied and created false accounts of him being the abuser."

It was reported back in 2019 that Depp had called on Warner Bros. to remove Heard from the first Aquaman film, in which she portrayed superheroine and warrior Mera. However, this didn't come to pass, and Heard recently confirmed she will reprise the role in the upcoming sequel. The petition started trending again -- and currently sits at 1.6 million signatures -- after Depp lost a libel case in early November against The Sun.

Following the ruling on the libel case, which was over a headline that referred to Depp as a "wife beater," Warner Bros. asked the actor to resign from Fantastic Beasts 3. While Depp obliged, the nature of his contract means Warner Bros. still needs to pay the actor's $10 million salary, as he'd already filmed a scene. Depp tried to appeal the case, but Judge Andrew Nicol ruled against him last week. Nicol denied Depp's appeal because he determined it did not have "a reasonable prospect of success." The judge also ruled that the actor must pay an initial ¬£628,000 ($837,437) in legal fees to The Sun.

Directed by James Wan, Aquaman 2 stars Jason Momoa as Aquaman, Amber Heard as Mera, Patrick Wilson as Ocean Master and Yahya Abdul-Mateen II as Black Manta. The film is currently scheduled to arrive in theaters on Dec. 16, 2022.

‚ÄòAquaman 2‚Äô Producer Explains Why Fan Campaign to Fire Amber Heard Was Rejected
https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/aquaman-2-amber-heard-peter-safran-fan-pressure-1234990820/

Aquaman¬†producer Peter Safran explained why online efforts to get¬†Amber Heard¬†removed from the superhero sequel were dismissed by the film‚Äôs creative team.
Heard plays aquatic warrior Mera in the franchise and has been the target of an intense lobbying campaign on social media largely driven by Johnny Depp supporters in the wake of the actors‚Äô tumultuous divorce.

After the trial verdict, Warner Bros. released Depp from the upcoming¬†Fantastic Beasts¬†sequel, with actor Mads Mikkelsen taking over the role of Gellert Grindelwald. The¬†Fantastic Beasts¬†recasting seemed to help fuel Depp supporters who insisted that Heard likewise get ousted from the upcoming¬†Aquaman¬†sequel.

David Ayer Blasts ‚ÄòSuicide Squad‚Äô: ‚ÄúThe Studio Cut Is Not My Movie‚Äù
https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/suicide-squad-david-ayer-warner-bros-1234990360/

Suicide Squad¬†director David Ayer is taking his criticism of the released version of his comic book film to a new level.
With James Gunn‚Äôs upcoming reboot¬†The Suicide Squad¬†drawing early praise¬†‚Äî and comparisons to Ayer‚Äôs disappointing 2016 effort ‚Äî Ayer accused Warner Bros. of dramatically recutting his film from his original vision.

‚ÄúI put my life into¬†Suicide Squad,‚Äù David Ayer wrote in a lengthy tweet titled ‚ÄúMy Turn.‚Äù ‚ÄúI made something amazing. My cut is intricate and emotional journey with some bad people who are shit on and discarded (a theme that resonates in my soul). The studio cut is not my movie. Read that again. And my cut is not the 10 week director‚Äôs cut ‚Äî it‚Äôs a fully mature edit by Lee Smith standing on the incredible work by John Gilroy. It‚Äôs all Steven Price‚Äôs brilliant score, with not a single radio song in the whole thing. It has traditional character arcs, amazing performances, a solid third-act resolution. A handful of people have seen it.‚Äù

‚ÄòAquaman 2‚Äô Producer Explains Why Fan Campaign to Fire Amber Heard Was Rejected
https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/aquaman-2-amber-heard-peter-safran-fan-pressure-1234990820/

Aquaman¬†producer Peter Safran explained why online efforts to get¬†Amber Heard¬†removed from the superhero sequel were dismissed by the film‚Äôs creative team.
Heard plays aquatic warrior Mera in the franchise and has been the target of an intense lobbying campaign on social media largely driven by Johnny Depp supporters in the wake of the actors‚Äô tumultuous divorce.

After the trial verdict, Warner Bros. released Depp from the upcoming¬†Fantastic Beasts¬†sequel, with actor Mads Mikkelsen taking over the role of Gellert Grindelwald. The¬†Fantastic Beasts¬†recasting seemed to help fuel Depp supporters who insisted that Heard likewise get ousted from the upcoming¬†Aquaman¬†sequel.

David Ayer Blasts ‚ÄòSuicide Squad‚Äô: ‚ÄúThe Studio Cut Is Not My Movie‚Äù
https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/suicide-squad-david-ayer-warner-bros-1234990360/

Suicide Squad¬†director David Ayer is taking his criticism of the released version of his comic book film to a new level.
With James Gunn‚Äôs upcoming reboot¬†The Suicide Squad¬†drawing early praise¬†‚Äî and comparisons to Ayer‚Äôs disappointing 2016 effort ‚Äî Ayer accused Warner Bros. of dramatically recutting his film from his original vision.

‚ÄúI put my life into¬†Suicide Squad,‚Äù David Ayer wrote in a lengthy tweet titled ‚ÄúMy Turn.‚Äù ‚ÄúI made something amazing. My cut is intricate and emotional journey with some bad people who are shit on and discarded (a theme that resonates in my soul). The studio cut is not my movie. Read that again. And my cut is not the 10 week director‚Äôs cut ‚Äî it‚Äôs a fully mature edit by Lee Smith standing on the incredible work by John Gilroy. It‚Äôs all Steven Price‚Äôs brilliant score, with not a single radio song in the whole thing. It has traditional character arcs, amazing performances, a solid third-act resolution. A handful of people have seen it.‚Äù

snippet.title: Amber Heard confirms role in 'Aquaman 2,' criticizes 'paid campaigns' to remove her from sequel
snippet.description: It's official. Amber Heard will be returning to "Aquaman 2."On Thursday, Heard confirmed to Entertainment Weekly¬†that she would be reprising her role as Mera¬†in the Warner Bros. sequel to the 2018¬†superhero film."I'm super excited about the amount of fan love and the amount of fan appreciation that 'Aquaman' has acquired and that it has garnered so much excitement for 'Aquaman' and Mera that it means we'll be coming back," Heard said.¬†"I'm so excited to film that."Some on social media¬†speculated whether Heard would return¬†to¬†"Aquaman 2," after a viral Change.org petition titled "Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2"¬†called for Warner Bros. and DC Entertainment to "remove Heard from their 'Aquaman 2' film project." As of Friday, the petition received over 1 million signatures.The outcry came after Warner Bros. requested¬†Johnny Depp resign from his role in the "Fantastic Beasts" franchise,¬†which he announced on Nov. 6.¬†His exit from the fantasy film came days after he lost his lengthy libel case against the British tabloid The Sun, who branded Depp a "wife beater" while reporting on his marriage with¬†Heard.Johnny Depp exits 'Fantastic Beasts' franchiseJason Momoa reveals he was 'completely in debt' after 'Game of Thrones'The "Pirates of the Caribbean" actor has maintained his innocence and intends to appeal, and Heard explained the upheaval has not cost her her role.¬†"Paid rumors and paid campaigns on social media don't dictate [casting decisions] because they have no basis in reality," Heard added. "Only the fans actually made¬†'Aquaman' and 'Aquaman 2' happen. I'm excited to get started next year."A U.K. judge ruled last week the¬†2018 article in The Sun¬†was not libelous after a contentious legal showdown this summer.¬†In 2018, Depp sued The Sun‚Äôs publisher, News Group Newspapers.¬†He strongly denied¬†all of Heard's allegations, countering that she was the abuser in their relationship.¬†Their marriage, Depp¬†told Heard several times, was "a crime scene waiting to happen," he testified.Judge Andrew Nicol delivered his verdict in writing without a hearing¬†‚Äì due to the coronavirus¬†‚Äì at the High Court in London, dismissing Depp's complaint against The Sun and finding that "the great majority" of Amber Heard's claims of assault could be "proved to the civil standard."¬†A lawyer for Depp, 57, described the decision as ‚Äúperverse as it is bewildering.‚Äù‚ÄúThe judgment is so flawed that it would be ridiculous for Mr. Depp not to appeal this decision,‚Äù Jenny Afia said in a statement to USA TODAY.An attorney for Heard, meanwhile, said the verdict was ‚Äúnot a surprise‚Äù for anyone who followed the trial.The Sun called the decision a ‚Äústunning victory for press freedom‚Äù and said that it had stood up and campaigned for victims of domestic abuse for more than 20 years.loses libel case against British tabloid that branded him a 'wife beater' to Amber HeardContributing: Maria Puente

It seems like everyone is turning against Amber Heard. Including the actors in the movie such as Jason Momoa, Nicole Kidman, William Dafoe, etc. The Johnny Depp Amber Heard legal battle is still at the forefront of celebrity news.

snippet.title: Jason Momoa SECRETLY Dislikes Working Alongside Amber Heard?!
snippet.description:
The filming for the upcoming DC Extended Universe film Aquaman and The Lost Kingdom has finally started, and fans were not happy about it. Well in fact, for a moment, they should have been happy, because this second installment is one of the most awaited films of 2022. When the first movie aired in theaters in 2018, fans were mesmerized by its cinematic wonder, and were already craving for more. However, due to a conflict that the film has gotten itself into, it is now pretty much a movie that almost everybody wants to cancel. How did this happen, you ask? Well for all of you who are newbies in the Johnny Depp and Amber Heard whirlwind of a case, let me just tell you that Amber Heard was able to reprise her role in the upcoming DCEU film franchise despite being involved in an ongoing case with Johnny Depp and their messy aftermath of a marriage. Apart from this, Johnny Depp had also been fired by Warner Brothers, the same production Aquaman is under, and has also been taken out from one of his most famous and commercially successful movies of all time: the Pirates of the Caribbean series.  So now that it has been decided that Warner Brothers will indeed keep Amber Heard despite all the allegations she is currently facing and despite all the unpleasant comments she is currently receiving. Fans are now wondering how her costars will take this news, especially the face and front of the whole movie, Jason Momoa. Some say that Jason actually secretly dislikes working with Amber Heard in their upcoming movie. But is this true? Let‚Äôs find out in this video. But before that, make sure first to hit that subscribe button and smash that notification bell for more updates. Let‚Äôs dive in!

The first day of filming of the new movie installment Aquaman and The Lost Kingdom was expected to be big news to its vieweers, but rather, it turned out to be a big waste. What made it an even larger disappointment for Warner Brothers is that the first Aquaman movie turned out to be a major blockbuster success in 2018, reaching 1.184 billion dollars, with a production budget of only 160 to 200 million dollars. That‚Äôs a lot of profit! However, Amber Heard‚Äôs involvement in the film has caused fans to turn their backs on the most awaited franchise.

But amidst all these, what are Amber‚Äôs co-stars thinking about the issue? Does it affect their interaction knowing all about Amber‚Äôs situation? And especially now that Amber has announced her newborn baby, who was born out of surrogacy, what do her colleagues at her Aquaman movie filming think of it? Well, let‚Äôs hear some of Jason Momoa‚Äôs thoughts about it. Jason Momoa, of all people, is the one who will get a really bad experience out of this once this movie flops because of Amber Heard.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp 'Resigns' from Fantastic Beasts at Warner Bros.' Request [Explain in Hindi]
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp 'Resigns' from Fantastic Beasts at Warner Bros.' Request [Explain in Hindi]

Warner Bros. has requested that Johnny Depp resign from the role of Grindelwald in the Fantastic Beasts franchise, which the actor has agreed upon.

Warner Bros. has requested that Johnny Depp resigns from his role as Grindelwald in the Fantastic Beasts film franchise. The actor has said that he respects and has agreed to the request.

Depp released a short statement on Instagram where he addressed these details. "In light of recent events, I would like to make the following short statement," Depp wrote. "Firstly, I'd like to thank everybody who has gifted me with their support and loyalty. I have been humbled and moved by your many messages of love and concern, particularly over the last few days. Secondly, I wish to let you know that I have been asked to resign by Warner Bros. from my role as Grindelwald in Fantastic Beasts and I have respected and agreed to that request. Finally, I wish to say this. The surreal judgment of the court in the U.K. will not change my fight to tell the truth and I confirm that I plan to appeal. My resolve remains strong and I intend to prove that the allegations against me are false. My life and career will not be defined by this moment in time. Thank you for reading.

Johnny Depp officially lost his libel trial against the Rupert Murdoch-owned British newspaper, The Sun, at the beginning of November. The Fantastic Beasts actor had filed the suit after the tabloid repeated claims by Depp's ex-wife, Aquaman star Amber Heard, that the Pirates of the Caribbean star was physically abusive towards her during their tumultuous, short-lived marriage.

Judge Andrew Nicol explained his decision: "The claimant [Depp] has not succeeded in his action for libel. Although he has proved the necessary elements of his cause of action in libel, the defendants have shown that what they published in the meaning which I have held the words to bear was substantially true." Nicol goes on further to note, "I have reached these conclusions having examined in detail the 14 incidents on which the defendants rely as well as the overarching considerations which the claimant submitted I should take into account."

In his ruling, Nicol actually collected all 14 allegations made by either Depp or The Sun (via Heard herself, whose claims the newspapers were relying on for their article) and determined whether he believed Heard, Depp or neither of them. Ultimately, after determining that Depp was mostly at fault in 12 of the 14 allegations, Nicol determined that The Sun had successfully argued that it was reasonable for the paper to refer to Depp as a "wife-beater."

snippet.title: Warner Bros. Gives Johnny Depp the Boot From¬†Fantastic Beasts
snippet.description: Johnny Depp is out from the Harry Potter spinoff Fantastic Beasts series, where he played Gellert Grindelwald. Depp revealed the news in an Instagram post on November 6, days after he lost a libel case against British tabloid The Sun. In a typewritten note posted to Instagram, he claimed Warner Bros. asked him to resign from the series, which is currently shooting its third movie and has plans for two more. He also claimed he would appeal his case, over the paper‚Äôs claims that he was a ‚Äúwife beater‚Äù in coverage of his alleged abuse toward ex-wife Amber Heard. ‚ÄúThe surreal judgment of the court in the U.K. will not change my fight to tell the truth and I confirm that I plan to appeal,‚Äù he wrote. ‚ÄúMy resolve remains strong and I intend to prove that the allegations against me are false. My life and career will not be defined by this moment in time.‚Äù Heard‚Äôs American lawyers previously responded in a statement to Entertainment Tonight. ‚ÄúVery soon, we will be presenting even more voluminous evidence in the U.S.,‚Äù Elaine Charlson Bredehoft told ET. ‚ÄúWe are committed to obtaining justice for Amber Heard in the U.S. Court and defending Ms. Heard‚Äôs Right to Free Speech.‚Äù   Depp‚Äôs role in the series has been controversial since preparations for the 2018 sequel The Crimes of Grindelwald. In November 2017, a year before the film premiered, director David Yates defended Depp‚Äôs inclusion and called the abuse allegations against him ‚Äúa dead issue.‚Äù  Update, 4:30 p.m.: The third Fantastic Beasts movie has been pushed from November 12, 2021, to summer 2022, Warner Bros. told Variety in a statement. The company also confirmed Depp‚Äôs former role of Gellert Grindelwald will be recast. Where‚Äôs a time-turner when you need one?  Update, November 9: The Hollywood Reporter has more details on Depp‚Äôs ouster, with sources telling the magazine that Johnny Depp had just shot one scene after filming began on September 20. According to The Hollywood Reporter, Warner Bros. waited until the judgment came down to cut ties with Depp ‚Äî who will still be paid his full salary for the project because of his pay-or-play contract. The third Fantastic Beasts movie, sans Depp, is now officially set for July 15, 2022.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp Tried To Get Amber Heard Replaced On Aquaman
snippet.description:
Subscribe I n  News English YouTube Channel To All The Big News Of The World.

Johnny Depp attempted to have ex-wife Amber Heard replaced on Aquaman. Depp and Heard were married from 2015-2017, and their relationship continues to have a major impact on the entertainment industry. The two made headlines for legal issues both during and after their marriage. Last month, Depp lost a lawsuit against The Sun, which called him a "wifebeater" in a 2018 article. Following this decision, Depp was asked to resign from the upcoming film Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them 3, where he was to reprise his role as Gellert Grindelwald. Despite only filming one scene, Depp received millions for his work on the movie.

Following Depp's exit from the Fantastic Beasts franchise, a subset of fans have similarly called for Heard to be fired from Aquaman 2. The actor starred as Mera in the first movie and will play the part again in the sequel. Last month, a petition titled "Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2" was started on Change.org. It quickly surpassed one million signatures and now sits at over 1.7 million. Shortly after, Heard debunked rumors Mera would be recast in the film, stating, "I'm excited to get started next year." Now, it seems those who signed the petition aren't the only ones who had an interest in having Heard replaced in the Aquaman franchise.

According to a new article from THR, at one point, Depp told his sister, Christi Dembrowski, a producer with pull at Warner Bros., that he wanted Heard "replaced on the WB film." In the process of the trial, Depp revealed the film in question was Aquaman.

The reveal about Depp comes after a similar report last year alleged the same. Though this more concrete information is shocking, it also lines up with what's already known about Depp and Heard's volatile relationship. Ultimately, it seems Depp's attempts to interfere with Heard's career amounted to nothing, as the actor remained a part of Aquaman. Still, the news is disconcerting to say the least, especially considering the power Depp once wielded in the industry. It's clear he was willing to use any sway he had against Heard, which is troubling.

It remains to be seen if this reveal about Depp will have any impact on Heard's future in the DC Extended Universe. If anything, it seems to reinforce Warner Bros' commitment to Heard. If Depp did follow through with contacting the studio through his sister, apparently his request was denied. Though there have been new developments in the last year or so, this could bode well for Heard's role in the next Aquaman movie.

snippet.title: Exigen cambiar a Amber Heard por Emilia Clarke para "Aquaman 2"
snippet.description:
Los fan√°ticos no se cansan de pedir que sea la camale√≥nica brit√°nica Emilia Clarke quien interprete a la nueva princesa de Atlantis en la pr√≥xima entrega de Aquaman, y cabe mencionar que no es la primera vez que esto sucede.


Han sido ya varias las veces que mientras avanza el medi√°tico pleito legal entre Johnny Depp y Amber Heard, tanto los fans como las grandes empresas productoras del s√©ptimo arte, han estado decidiendo que hacer y que no, con sus respectivos actores y pel√≠culas venideras. 

Por ejemplo, sabemos que Warner Bros, pr√°cticamente oblig√≥ a Depp a retirarse de las filmaciones de la tercera entrega de la saga de "Animales Fant√°sticos", gracias a que el juez encargado del caso, dict√≥ a favor de la actriz, sin embargo, el papel de Mera en Aquaman 2 sigue estando intacto, aun que los fieles fans del actor han realizado gran cantidad de peticiones y han reunido millones de firmas para que esto sea posible. 


Sabemos tambi√©n que, desde que inicio todo el proceso legal en contra del actor, a partir de las acusaciones Jhonny fue despedido de varios empleos, y curiosamente Amber obtuvo papeles protag√≥nicos, como lo es el de la princesa Mera, en Aquaman, y a ra√≠z de esto obtuvo un nuevo s√©quito de fans e innumerables oportunidades, incluyendo desde luego la posibilidad de una gran secuela en el Universo Cinematogr√°fico de DC, la cual, es ahora mas que una realidad. 

Ahora, la nueva informaci√≥n obtenida, en torno a las resoluciones, se√±ala que el estudio de Warner no quiere deshacerse de la actriz por miedo a que las relaciones p√∫blicas de la empresa se entorpezcan, ya que despu√©s de todo, ella fue declarada triunfadora en el juicio de Londres y por lo tanto es considerada de manera oficial como una v√≠ctima de vi0lencia dom√©stica.

"Que Warner Bros. elimine a una actriz que fue v√≠ct1ma de abus0 conyugal crear√° relaciones p√∫blicas a√∫n peores, eso temen los ejecutivos, a pesar de lo que tambi√©n se le acusa a ella", a mencionado un productor al respecto. 


Sin embargo, los fans no se cansan de intentar que se haga algo al respecto, y una vez mas han reunido sus fuerzas para pedirle a los directivos y  productores de Warner Bros Company que se deshagan de Amber y Emilia Clarke tome su lugar para el papel de la princesa Mera en la secuela de Aquaman. 


Como sabemos, han elegido a Clarke debido a la enorme qu√≠mica esc√©nica que tiene con Jason Momoa, el protagonista, tal y como ya lo han demostrado, trabajando juntos en "Juego de tronos", donde podemos ver que funcionan demasiado bien laborando de la mano, sin duda, la qu√≠mica es innegable.

Por tal motivo, el artista digital Bosslogic, un experto en el arte del fan cast, ha creado un dise√±o en el que se muestra a la Madre de Dragones con la corona y la ic√≥nica melena pelirroja dela fuerte y bella princesa Mera, y el resultado es de lo m√°s sorprendente, ya que, gracias a sus facciones y sus ojos verdes, realmente si nos podemos imaginar a Clarke como la gobernante de los mares. 

Por el momento, Amber Heard sigue estando m√°s que confirmada para la secuela de Aquaman, ya que lo ha confirmado recientemente en una entrevista para importantes medios brit√°nicos, aunque eso podr√≠a cambiar en las pr√≥ximas semanas, ya que la petici√≥n para su despido ya recoge m√°s de un mill√≥n firmas del p√∫blico.


Y, en caso de ser sustituida, Clarke ser√≠a una gran opci√≥n, tal y como muestra la imagen de Bosslogic, en la que resalta su intensa y poderosa mirada.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp ‚Äòwanted Amber Heard axed from Aquaman‚Äô
snippet.description: Claims Johnny Depp wanted Amber Heard replaced in her Aquaman role have resurfaced, following his highly-publicised libel trial.  ¬†Earlier this year the Pirates Of The Caribbean star lost his trial against The Sun‚Äôs publisher NGN Newspapers, over an article that labelled him a ‚Äòwife-beater‚Äô. He has since applied to have the decision overturned.  ¬†During the trial it was put forward to the court that Depp had demanded former wife Heard ‚Äì who he was married to from 2015 to 2017 ‚Äì be stripped of her role as Mera in Warner Bros‚Äô Aquaman sequel, with the details re-emerging this week in a lengthy profile on the star.  ¬†As was reported by Press Association during the trial in July, Sasha Wass QC, for NGN, told the court ‚Äòfrom the moment Ms Heard petitioned for divorce and for a restraining order, the full brute force of Mr Depp and his PR machine was engaged‚Äô.  ¬†She said: ‚ÄòReports appeared in the press suggesting that she was a gold digger. Mr Depp personally set out to damage her career.‚Äô  ¬†Wass said that after Depp sent a text to his sister saying: ‚ÄòI want her replaced on that WB film‚Äô ‚Äì a reference to the Warner Brothers film Aquaman ‚Äì ‚Äòa petition garnered the support of 400,000 people [quoted at the time of trial] to have Ms Heard removed from the film‚Äô.  ¬†According to The Hollywood Reporter, which published the profile this week, the messages were sent to Depp‚Äôs sister, producer Christi Dembrowski, ‚Äòwho previously had a deal with the studio and was influential there‚Äô.   ¬†It comes amid a petition, titled ‚ÄòRemove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2‚Ä≤, which has reached 1.7million signatures.   ¬†However, the star, who appeared in the 2018 superhero film opposite Jason Momoa, confirmed last month she would be returning for the sequel which is set to film next year.  ¬†She recently said: ‚ÄòI‚Äôm super excited about the amount of fan love and the amount of fan appreciation that Aquaman has acquired and that it has garnered so much excitement for Aquaman and Mera that it means we‚Äôll be coming back. I‚Äôm so excited to film that.‚Äô  ¬†The petition, started by Jeanne Larson, alleged that Amber is a ‚Äòknown and proven abuser‚Äô, and claims that she has ‚Äòsystematically crusaded to ruin Depp in Hollywood‚Äô.  ¬†Both Depp and Heard alleged abuse by the other during the libel trial, and also both denied allegations against them.  ¬†A judge eventually ruled in favour of The Sun, saying they were accurate in calling Depp a ‚Äòwife beater‚Äô in an article headline.  ¬†In the wake of his trial loss, Depp resigned from his role as Gellert Grindelwald in the Fantastic Beasts franchise, after being asked to by Warner Bros, and has since been replaced by Mads Mikkelsen however the profile claimed he was still paid $16million (¬£12m) for the one scene he‚Äôd shot before stepping down.   ¬†He continues to remain in advertisements for Dior‚Äôs Sauvage fragrance.

snippet.title: Emilia responds to replacing Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Aquaman 2 starring Jason Momoa is amongst the most awaited films in the DC Extended Universe. Mera was played by Amber Heard in the first Aquaman movie. Jason Momoa was seen in the role of Arthur Curry AKA Aquaman. Willem Dafoe played Vulko, Patrick Wilson played Orm / Ocean Master, Yahya Abdul-Mateen II played Black Manta, Dolph Lundgren played Nereus, Nicole Kidman played Atlanna, Temuera Morrison played Tom Curry, and Ludi Lin played Captain Murk were among the other notable cast members.

But Amber Heard‚Äôs court struggle with ex-husband Johnny Depp has received a lot of public attention in recent years. Despite the fact that the pair had split in 2017, judicial processes in respect to domestic violence accusations and Johnny Depp‚Äôs libel action were still ongoing in 2021.

In the middle of the libel action, Warner Bros. withdrew Johnny Depp from his part in the Fantastic Beasts film trilogy. As per We Got This Covered, Amber Heard supporters turned upon her due to the legal fight, and many joined a Change.org petition to have her withdrawn from the Aquaman 2 movie.

This all began when Amber Heard‚Äôs audio confession to physical attack leaked online. Previously, Johnny Depp was viewed as the culprit, however, this flipped things around. Fans of the Fantastic Beasts star staged protests to have Heard removed from Aquaman. Soon afterward, this was reported that the DC creators were thinking about that as well.

But Amber Heard‚Äôs court struggle with ex-husband Johnny Depp has received a lot of public attention in recent years. Despite the fact that the pair had split in 2017, judicial processes in respect to domestic violence accusations and Johnny Depp‚Äôs libel action were still ongoing in 2021.

In the middle of the libel action, Warner Bros. withdrew Johnny Depp from his part in the Fantastic Beasts film trilogy. As per We Got This Covered, Amber Heard supporters turned upon her due to the legal fight, and many joined a Change.org petition to have her withdrawn from the Aquaman 2 movie.

This all began when Amber Heard‚Äôs audio confession to physical attack leaked online. Previously, Johnny Depp was viewed as the culprit, however, this flipped things around. Fans of the Fantastic Beasts star staged protests to have Heard removed from Aquaman. Soon afterward, this was reported that the DC creators were thinking about that as well.

snippet.title: Amber Heard confirms role in 'Aquaman 2,' criticizes 'paid campaigns' to remove her from sequel
snippet.description: It's official. Amber Heard will be returning to "Aquaman 2."On Thursday, Heard confirmed to Entertainment Weekly¬†that she would be reprising her role as Mera¬†in the Warner Bros. sequel to the 2018¬†superhero film."I'm super excited about the amount of fan love and the amount of fan appreciation that 'Aquaman' has acquired and that it has garnered so much excitement for 'Aquaman' and Mera that it means we'll be coming back," Heard said.¬†"I'm so excited to film that."Some on social media¬†speculated whether Heard would return¬†to¬†"Aquaman 2," after a viral Change.org petition titled "Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2"¬†called for Warner Bros. and DC Entertainment to "remove Heard from their 'Aquaman 2' film project." As of Friday, the petition received over 1 million signatures.The outcry came after Warner Bros. requested¬†Johnny Depp resign from his role in the "Fantastic Beasts" franchise,¬†which he announced on Nov. 6.¬†His exit from the fantasy film came days after he lost his lengthy libel case against the British tabloid The Sun, who branded Depp a "wife beater" while reporting on his marriage with¬†Heard.Johnny Depp exits 'Fantastic Beasts' franchiseJason Momoa reveals he was 'completely in debt' after 'Game of Thrones'The "Pirates of the Caribbean" actor has maintained his innocence and intends to appeal, and Heard explained the upheaval has not cost her her role.¬†"Paid rumors and paid campaigns on social media don't dictate [casting decisions] because they have no basis in reality," Heard added. "Only the fans actually made¬†'Aquaman' and 'Aquaman 2' happen. I'm excited to get started next year."A U.K. judge ruled last week the¬†2018 article in The Sun¬†was not libelous after a contentious legal showdown this summer.¬†In 2018, Depp sued The Sun‚Äôs publisher, News Group Newspapers.¬†He strongly denied¬†all of Heard's allegations, countering that she was the abuser in their relationship.¬†Their marriage, Depp¬†told Heard several times, was "a crime scene waiting to happen," he testified.Judge Andrew Nicol delivered his verdict in writing without a hearing¬†‚Äì due to the coronavirus¬†‚Äì at the High Court in London, dismissing Depp's complaint against The Sun and finding that "the great majority" of Amber Heard's claims of assault could be "proved to the civil standard."¬†A lawyer for Depp, 57, described the decision as ‚Äúperverse as it is bewildering.‚Äù‚ÄúThe judgment is so flawed that it would be ridiculous for Mr. Depp not to appeal this decision,‚Äù Jenny Afia said in a statement to USA TODAY.An attorney for Heard, meanwhile, said the verdict was ‚Äúnot a surprise‚Äù for anyone who followed the trial.The Sun called the decision a ‚Äústunning victory for press freedom‚Äù and said that it had stood up and campaigned for victims of domestic abuse for more than 20 years.loses libel case against British tabloid that branded him a 'wife beater' to Amber HeardContributing: Maria Puente

snippet.title: Amber Heard comments on Aquaman role as Johnny Depp fans call for star to be given the boot
snippet.description: Amber Heard has seemingly responded to Johnny Depp fans‚Äô campaign to have her axed from the upcoming Aquaman 2, following Depp‚Äôs libel trial loss in the UK.   ¬†Last week Depp stepped down from the role of Gellert Grindelwald in the Harry Potter spin-off Fantastic Beasts, after being asked to do so by Warner Bros following the trial.  ¬†Not long after, his fans started a Change.org. petition to have Heard, who was married to Depp from 2015 to 2017, dropped from her role in the Aquaman sequel, which has so far reached more than 1million signatures.  ¬†Heard has now commented on her role in the DC film in an interview with  Weekly in which she appeared to rubbish any rumour she wouldn‚Äôt be making her return as Mera.  ¬†She told the publication: ‚ÄòI‚Äôm super excited about the amount of fan love and the amount of fan appreciation that Aquaman has acquired and that it has garnered so much excitement for Aquaman and Mera that it means we‚Äôll be coming back.  ¬†‚ÄòI‚Äôm so excited to film that.‚Äô  ¬†The actor added production hopes to get underway sometime in 2021.  ¬†Her comments follow the judge‚Äôs findings of Depp‚Äôs trial against The Sun‚Äôs publishers after he sued following an article which branded the actor a ‚Äòwife-beater‚Äô.  ¬†In delivering his verdict, Justice Nicol found that 12 of the 14 alleged incidents of domestic violence did occur.  ¬†Depp‚Äôs lawyers said they want to appeal the ‚Äòperverse‚Äô verdict.   ¬†In a handwritten statement last week, the Pirates Of The Caribbean star confirmed he was leaving the Fantastic Beasts franchise.  ¬†Depp wrote on Instagram: ‚ÄòFirstly, I‚Äôd like to thank everybody who has gifted me with their support and loyalty.  ¬†‚ÄòI have been humbled and moved by your many messages of love and concern, particularly over the last few days.  ¬†‚ÄòSecondly, I wish to let you know that I have been asked to resign by Warner Bros from my role as Grindelwald in Fantastic Beasts and I have respected and agreed to that request.  ¬†‚ÄòFinally, I wish to say this. The surreal judgement of the court in the UK will not change my fight to tell the truth and I confirm that I plan to appeal.‚Äô  ¬†Despite stepping down, the actor will reportedly get his full salary for the film, for which he shot just one scene.  ¬†According to the Hollywood Reporter, Depp had a ‚Äòpay-or-play contract‚Äô, which requires that he be fully compensated whether or not the film is made and even if it is recast.   ¬†The star is believed to have been on an eight-figure salary, and was the highest paid out of his co-stars Eddie Redmayne, who plays Newt Scamander, and Jude Law, who plays Dumbledore.

Pictures y el director James Wan nos traen una aventura llena de acci√≥n que abarca el vasto y sorprendente mundo submarino de los siete mares, "Aquaman", protagonizada por Jason Momoa en el papel principal. La pel√≠cula revela la historia de origen de Arthur Curry, mitad humano y mitad atlante, y lo lleva al viaje de su vida, uno que no solo lo forzar√° a enfrentar qui√©n es en realidad, sino a descubrir si es digno de qui√©n es √©l. naci√≥ para ser ... un rey.

La pel√≠cula tambi√©n est√° protagonizada por Amber Heard ("Liga De La Justicia", "Magic Mike XXL") como Mera, una guerrera feroz y aliada de Aquaman a lo largo de su viaje; el nominado al Oscar Willem Dafoe ("Pelot√≥n", "Spider-Man 2") como Vulko, consejero del trono Atlante; Patrick Wilson (Saga de "El Conjuro", "Watchmen") como Orm / Ocean Master, el actual Rey de la Atl√°ntida; Dolph Lundgren (Saga de "Los Indestructibles") como Nereus, rey de la tribu Atlante Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II ("Baywatch", "The Get Down" de Netflix) como la vengativa Black Manta; y la ganadora del Oscar Nicole Kidman ("Las Horas", "Lion") como la madre de Arthur, Atlanna; as√≠ como Ludi Lin ("Power Rangers") como el Capit√°n Murk, Comando Atlante; y Temuera Morrison ("Star Wars: Episodio II - El Ataque de los Clones", "Linterna Verde") como el padre de Arthur, Tom Curry.

Wan dirige el gui√≥n de David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick ("El Conjuro 2") y Will Beall ("Gangster Squad: Brigada de √âlite", "D√≠a de Entrenamiento" de TV), una historia de Geoff Johns y James Wan y Will Beall, basada en personajes de DC , Aquaman creado por Paul Norris y Mort Weisinger. La pel√≠cula est√° producida por Peter Safran y Rob Cowan, con Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns y Walter Hamada como productores ejecutivos.

El equipo de Wan detr√°s de escena incluye colaboradores tan frecuentes como el director de fotograf√≠a nominado al Oscar Don Burgess ("El Conjuro 2", "Forrest Gump"), su cinco veces editor Kirk Morri ("Saga El Conjuro", "R√°pidos y Furiosos 7", las pel√≠culas "La Noche Del Demonio") y el dise√±ador de producci√≥n Bill Brzeski ("R√°pidos y Furiosos 7"). A ellos se unen la dise√±adora de vestuario Kym Barrett (trilog√≠a "Matrix", "El Sorprendente Hombre Ara√±a") y el compositor Rupert Gregson-Williams ("Mujer Maravilla").
Warner Bros. Pictures presenta una producci√≥n de la compa√±√≠a Safran, una pel√≠cula de James Wan, "Aquaman". La pel√≠cula llegar√° a los cines en diciembre de 2018, en 3D y 2D e IMAX, y ser√° distribuida por todo el mundo por Warner Bros. Pictures, Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

snippet.title: JOHNNY DEPP SHOCKS Amber Heard and Warner Brothers after THIS BOMBSHELL | Celebrity Craze
snippet.description:
JOHNNY DEPP SHOCKS Amber Heard and Warner Brothers after THIS Fantastic Beasts 3 BOMBSHELL | Celebrity Craze

In this video, Celebrity Craze shows J.K Rowling's Reaction to Losing Johnny Depp in the upcoming Fantastic Beasts And Where To Find Them Movie. As you know, Johnny has been replaced by Mads Mikkelsen and according to J.K. Rowling, this can literally destroy the movie series!

With the initial court date being pushed back, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard have been given some more time in order to gather more evidence for their individual cases. For quite some time, the two were firing evidence at each other in order to win in court. 

Ever since the recent release of the footage of the LAPD officers from the penthouse night of Amber Heard and Johnny Depp, things have not been looking all too bright for Amber Heard. Her team has been working tirelessly in order to back up her side, however Johnny Depp seems to have made the attempt to strike back.

Now she is chilling and taking photos on set of the new Aquaman 2 movie. Set to hit theaters in 2022. This is enraging a lot of Johnny Depp supporters.

snippet.title: GUESS Jeans - Fall 2011 Campaign - Featuring Amber Heard
snippet.description:
This Fall, GUESS once again partners with famed photographer, Ellen Von Unwerth, to shoot rising talent, Amber Heard, and Silvu Tulu, in a love story that makes the timeless tale between a saloon singer and a lone cowboy fresh and exciting. The classic, black-and-white images are reminiscent of the 1950's and 1960's western film classics that defined a generation.

Cuffed, skinny jeans, cropped denim jackets, knit bustiers and retro-inspired dresses set the tone for the campaign -- a sexy, love story. The men's pieces draw the viewer into the western traveler with his denim jackets and leather bombers, western inspired wovens and worn in jeans which serve to compliment the women's collection. 

Through a precise balance of close-up and scenic photographs, Ellen's lens transports the audience out west to an unidentified bus stop where a love story between the two leading characters begins to unfold. Whether it's a private glimpse of our heroine lounging in her seat, primping at a motel before her performance or the intimate shots of the characters connection unfolding - the campaign is shot in such a way that the viewer knows they are witnessing a life altering experience between the pair.

"Amber embodies the essence of the true GUESS girl with her natural beauty and all-American good looks," says Paul Marciano, Chief Executive Officer and Creative Director for Guess?, Inc. "The campaign, which was shot by Ellen Von Unwerth, is sure to become an American classic that will continue to define what the GUESS brand stands for." 

Paul Marciano, who built the global lifestyle brand along with his brother, Maurice, Chairman of the Board, in 1981, has been heralded as launching the careers of then-unknowns including Claudia Schiffer, Anna Nicole Smith, Laetitia Casta and more recently, Kate Upton and Alyssa Miller. His natural eye for discovering raw talent has led to some of the most recognizable and iconic images over the past thirty years.


Music:
Dale Earnhardt Jr Jr
"Simple Girl"
from the album It's A Corporate World
out now on Warner Bros Records

snippet.title: AQUAMAN ‚Äì Behind the Scenes ‚Äì Now Playing In Theaters
snippet.description:
www.Facebook.com/AquamanMovie
www.Twitter.com/AquamanMovie
www.Instagram.com/AquamanMovie
www.AquamanMovie.com

From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger.  The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Wan Film, ‚ÄúAquaman.‚Äù  The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018, in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

snippet.title: #43 || Warner Bros. Screwed Up
snippet.description:
One of the biggest news recently in Hollywood is probably the news about Johnny Depp being asked to leave Fantastic Beats 3 as Grindelwald but his ex-wife, Amber Heard was allowed to stay on for DC movies like Aquaman. Isn't that crazy? The Judge from the court case even threw out Johnny Depp's evidence even though it was a recording of Amber Heard admitting to hitting Johnny Depp. Hollywood is weird. But Warner Bros. did Johnny Depp dirty... Funny enough though, Warner Bros. still has to pay Johnny Depp his 8-figure salary even though he only filmed one scene in the movie.

snippet.title: AQUAMAN ‚Äì Final Trailer ‚Äì Warner Bros. UK Boom!!
snippet.description:

Twitter: https://mobile.twitter.com/ZackSnyderFrom Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.  The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (upcoming ‚ÄúBaywatch,‚Äù Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.  Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger.  The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.  Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù). Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Wan Film, ‚ÄúAquaman.‚Äù  The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018, in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.  #Aquaman2 #Aquamantrailer

snippet.title: Johnny Depp forderte Ambers "Aquaman"-Aus bei Warner Bros.
snippet.description:
Die Aufregung um Amber Heards (34) Aquaman-Rolle rei√üt nicht ab! Aufgrund der Aussagen der 34-J√§hrigen hat ihr Ex Johnny Depp (57) nicht nur seinen "Frauenschl√§ger"-Verleumdungsprozess gegen eine britische Zeitung verloren ‚Äì sondern auch seine Hauptrolle als Gellert Grindelwald im dritten Teil von Phantastische Tierwesen. Deshalb starteten seine Fans vor ein paar Wochen eine Petition daf√ºr, dass auch Amber ihre n√§chste gro√üe Rolle in "Aquaman 2" abgeben soll. Inzwischen hat die Forderung rund 1,7 Millionen Anh√§nger. Johnny selbst ging einen Schritt weiter: Er wollte seine Ex-Frau bereits aus dem ersten "Aquaman"-Teil streichen lassen! 
Das berichtet nun das Onlinemagazin The Hollywood Reporter, dem ein Brief von Johnny an seine Schwester Christi Dembrowski vorliegen soll. Letztere ist Filmproduzentin und hatte zu dem Zeitpunkt f√ºr Warner Bros. gearbeitet ‚Äì also f√ºr das Studio, das "Aquaman" produziert hat. Angeblich soll der 57-J√§hrige darin gefordert haben: "Ich will, dass sie in dem Film von Warner Bros. ersetzt wird." Wann genau das Schreiben entstanden und abgeschickt worden ist, ist nicht bekannt. Klar ist jedoch: Erfolg hatte der Schauspieler damit nicht. 
Die Comicverfilmung flimmerte weltweit im Jahr 2018 √ºber die Kinoleinw√§nde ‚Äì und mauserte sich schnell zu einem Riesenerfolg. So verzeichnete "Aquaman" bisher allein in Deutschland rund 1,9 Millionen Besucher. Amber spielt darin an der Seite von Game of Thrones-Hottie Jason Momoa (41) die Rolle der Meeresk√∂nigin Mera, die wohl auch in Teil zwei eine gro√üe Rolle spielen wird. 
K√∂nntet ihr euch die "Aquaman"-Reihe ohne Amber vorstellen?

snippet.title: AQUAMAN ‚Äì Extended Video ‚Äì Now Playing In Theaters
snippet.description:
www.Facebook.com/AquamanMovie
www.Twitter.com/AquamanMovie
www.Instagram.com/AquamanMovie
www.AquamanMovie.com

From Warner Bros. Pictures and director James Wan comes an action-packed adventure that spans the vast, visually breathtaking underwater world of the seven seas, ‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù starring Jason Momoa in the title role.  The film reveals the origin story of half-human, half-Atlantean Arthur Curry and takes him on the journey of his lifetime‚Äîone that will not only force him to face who he really is, but to discover if he is worthy of who he was born to be‚Ä¶a king.

The film also stars Amber Heard (‚ÄúJustice League,‚Äù ‚ÄúMagic Mike XXL‚Äù) as Mera, a fierce warrior and Aquaman‚Äôs ally throughout his journey; Oscar nominee Willem Dafoe (‚ÄúPlatoon,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpider-Man 2‚Äù) as Vulko, council to the Atlantean throne; Patrick Wilson (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúWatchmen‚Äù) as Orm/Ocean Master, the present King of Atlantis; Dolph Lundgren (‚ÄúThe Expendables‚Äù films) as Nereus, King of the Atlantean tribe Xebel; Yahya Abdul-Mateen II (Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Get Down‚Äù) as the vengeful Black Manta; and Oscar winner Nicole Kidman (‚ÄúThe Hours,‚Äù ‚ÄúLion‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs mom, Atlanna; as well as Ludi Lin (‚ÄúPower Rangers‚Äù) as Captain Murk, Atlantean Commando; and Temuera Morrison (‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode II ‚Äì Attack of the Clones,‚Äù ‚ÄúGreen Lantern‚Äù) as Arthur‚Äôs dad, Tom Curry.

Wan directs from a screenplay by David Leslie Johnson-McGoldrick (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2‚Äù) and Will Beall (‚ÄúGangster Squad,‚Äù TV‚Äôs ‚ÄúTraining Day‚Äù), story by Geoff Johns & James Wan and Will Beall, based on characters from DC, Aquaman created by Paul Norris and Mort Weisinger.  The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).

Warner Bros. Pictures Presents a Safran Company Production, a James Wan Film, ‚ÄúAquaman.‚Äù  The film is set to hit theaters on December 21, 2018, in 3D and 2D and IMAX, and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, a Warner Bros. Entertainment Company.

The film is produced by Peter Safran and Rob Cowan, with Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Jon Berg, Geoff Johns and Walter Hamada serving as executive producers.

Wan‚Äôs team behind the scenes includes such frequent collaborators as Oscar-nominated director of photography Don Burgess (‚ÄúThe Conjuring 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúForrest Gump‚Äù), his five-time editor Kirk Morri (‚ÄúThe Conjuring‚Äù films, ‚ÄúFurious 7,‚Äù the ‚ÄúInsidious‚Äù films), and production designer Bill Brzeski (‚ÄúFurious 7‚Äù).  They are joined by costume designer Kym Barrett (‚ÄúThe Matrix‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúThe Amazing Spider-Man‚Äù) and composer Rupert Gregson-Williams (‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù).
